        Deprecated. 
        Splitting parcel processus. It get the usual parcel schema and add the "split" field in order to determine in the parcel will be splited or not. All the parcels are then split.
        Parameters:
        parcelIn - : collection of parcels
        tmpFolder - : a folder to store temporary files
        maximalArea - : area of the parcel under which the parcel won't be anymore cut
        maximalWidth - : width of the parcel under which the parcel won't be anymore cut
        epsilon - :
        extBlock -
        streetWidth - : with of the street composing the street network
        decompositionLevelWithoutStreet - : number of last iteration row for which no street network is generated
        forceStreetAccess - : force the access to the road for each parcel. Not working good yet.
        Returns:
        a collection of subdivised parcels
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

        Split the parcels into sub parcels. The parcel that are going to be cut must have a field "SPLIT" with the value of 1. A dirty conversion is made from GeoTools format to GeOxygene format because the functions that must translate them doesn't work yet.
        Parameters:
        toSplit - SimpleFeatureCollection of parcels
        maximalArea - Area of the parcel under which the parcel won't be anymore cut
        maximalWidth - Width of the parcel under which the parcel won't be anymore cut
        streetEpsilon -
        noise -
        extBlock -
        streetWidth - With of the street composing the street network
        decompositionLevelWithoutStreet - Number of last iteration row for which no street network is generated
        forceStreetAccess - Force the access to the road for each parcel. Not working good yet.
        tmpFolder - A folder to store temporary files
        Returns:
        a collection of subdivised parcels
